Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Solvang
Description: A sunny and idyllic Danish town, which gives a sense of living in an Hans Christian Andersen fairy tale.

Name: Hearst Castle
Description: It was the private castle of  the family of William Randolph Hearst, an American newspaper magnate, which is the most luxurious and resplendent castle in California.

Name: Pfeiffer Beach
Description: The sea sand here is purple, formed by eroding manganese garnet particles,  which is the only purple beach in the world. Moreover, the best time to visit should be in the evening, that the setting sun will shine on the purple beach through the gate-shaped reef.

Name: Bixby Creek Bridge
Description: One of the landmarks of Big Sur, which is photogenic and breathtaking! Its artificial shape and natural sea  background are an excellent match.

Name: Pigeon Point Lighthouse
Description: The tallest lighthouse on the Pacific coast and is still in use today, which instructs ships to avoid danger.
